Package: gpplot
Type: Package
Version: 0.0.1
Title: Create beautiful 'ggplot2' Objects in a Fast and Intuitive Syntax 
Description: This is a set of tools for creating plots using 'ggplot2' and related packages. 
  The 'ggplot2' style allows to create wonderful plots but its syntax of can be repetitive 
  and sometimes counterintuitive. The package 'gpplot' try to solve this problem in standard cases 
  related to Bayesian statistics.
Authors@R: c(person("Giovanni", "Poli", role=c("aut", "cre"), email="giovanni.poli@unifi.it"))
Maintainer: Giovanni Poli <giovanni.poli@unifi.it>
LazyLoad: true
Depends:
    R(>= 3.5)
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: 
    ggdendro,
    ggplot2,
    scales
